result.name: Mak's Noodle

reviews.text: Tourist trap. Go to the place with the only Chinese sign two doors away. This place was too expensive for tiny portions and also extremely rude and pushy, trying to get us to order and eat and pay as fast as possible
Three wontons are great, the noodles have excellent texture and the soup brings it all together. The servings are small but make up for it in quality
The much more crowded, local place next door is a little better (wontons taste fresher), but this is a nicer place to sit down at, and the same price and portion sizes.
Great taste but portions were small for their price

Big name Wanton noodle shop that has 6 outlets in Hong Kong, 2 outlets in Singapore. The noodle is really springy but the Wanton was a bit let down because of high MSG content and too much pepper... This outlet at Mongkok is relatively compact but not crowded when I was there. Price wise, HKD38 for a standard Wanton noodle, which is a typical price range for this type of shops at Tsim Sha Tsui /Mong Kok. Another local Wanton noodle shop has more crowd. May be locals know best!

result.name: Mak Man Kee Noodle Shop

reviews.text: Fantastic! The aunty was very friendly, the portion is just nice for me. The 抄手 is amazing! And I will definitely come back again next time! Sorry I totally forgot to take pictures when I saw the food 😅
Had dry dumpling noodles for a quick lunch. Noodles was smokey, dumplings was tasty and the soup was flavoursome. Highly recommend this place for a 20 minute lunch.
Food tastes gd but vy poor service and staff are rude. Expensive for a bowl of small noodles.

The 5 star michellin noodle stall that is worth the queue. The beef brisket noodle and the wonton soup will take you to delicacy heaven. 
The pork knuckle noodle is ok but it will be a 1 time experience only for me. 
Please do note that narurally i am not a fan of chinese sweet soy sauce pork knuckle so do check on others review on the knuckle. 

Going to Temple street?
Be sure to visit here before you do your souvenir shopping. 
You will not regret this.
Definitely one of the Top 3 wonton noodles shops in HK, and I've tried most of the famous ones. Mak Man Kee beats Chee Kei and Mak's

result.name: 麥文記麵家

reviews.text: 好食老字號👍🏽招牌雲吞麵值得一試
好吃😋

香港雲吞麵你又食過了沒有?
這家雲吞麵已經營超過半世紀 而且也很有名氣

這次來到佐敦來探店 去到的時間已過飯市
所以不太多人 很快就有位置坐了

·|鮮蝦雲吞麵^HKD$40
一碗雲吞麵裡面有5-6粒 裡面只有鮮蝦肉
肉質比較爽口岸彈牙 麵的份量剛剛好的~
而湯底也挻濃郁挻香的味道 飲了一兩口也不咸

[环境]
雖然已超過半世紀 但店裡裝修不太舊
依然保持傳統雲吞麵鋪的外表 具有香港特色
雖然地方比較淺窄 但人龍不斷可見其威力🤤

[服务]
店家的湯底經過8小時熬製而成 所以比較濃郁
而且雲吞的蝦也沒有將貨就價以保持品質
從而可見到商家的用心 希望我們食到好食物💪

result.name: 麥奀雲吞麵世家

reviews.text:
味道👍
新鮮👍
份量太少👎
服務👌
อาหารอร่อยมากกิมมิคของร้านแปะอยู่ด้านหน้าเมนูนั้นเลยพรุ่งนี้หนึบๆดิ้นคาปาก

隣のお店に入るつもりが間違えて来店(笑)
汁なしの海老の粉がかかった麺を食べたくてはいりました！

量がやや少な目でペロリと食べられました🍝
味は普通に美味しくて、飽きの来ない感じでした。
老舗のようなので味はたしかなのかな？

お茶がついてきますが無料なのにビックリしました。
他店では必ずお茶代はいってたので(^_^;)
唔係真係太好食，價錢又貴， 有好多地方好過去👎
地方太陝窄，要食两碗始可有感覺，員工禮貌多D，感受會好的
